==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Niepces process
<hw>Niep"ce's proc"ess</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Photog.)</fld> <def>A
process, now no longer used, invented by <person>J. N.
<etsep>Niepce</etsep></person>, a French chemist, in 1829. It depends
upon the action of light in rendering a thin layer of bitumen, with
which the plate is coated, insoluble.</def> <mark>[Obsolescent]</mark>
⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

